    {
        "url": "/quotes/bradley_a_smith_516378",
        "quote": "Every major federal campaign-finance-reform effort since 1943 has attempted to treat corporations and unions equally. If a limit applied to corporations, it applied to unions; if unions could form PACs, corporations could too; and so on. DISCLOSE is the first major campaign-finance bill that has not taken this approach.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Bradley A. Smith",
            "url": "/quotes/bradley_a_smith_516378"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Treat",
